message: separated react-native-controllers into an npm module

upgraded to react native 0.18, added support for passProps, changed tab icons to be packager assets, fixed issue with array of jsx children, fixed issue with insets where screens would draw under navigation bar
make sure we publish to public
release 1.2.4 hot fix for issues on reload
release 1.2.5 hot fix to solve reload problems once again

Fixed leak issue, the controllers registry was not cleared when a new root was set (issue #25).
Also promoted version to 1.3.3.
added protection from Null object when setting title image
changes in JS to support the breaking changes introduced in the transition to RN 0.25.1
lowercase prop names for external VC

Bug fix: in case there is a interactivePopGestureRecognizer, it prevents react-native from getting touch events on the left screen area that the gesture handles.
Overriding the delegate of the gesture prevents this from happening while keeping the gesture intact.
notification: fixed animation damping not taken into account

Fixed a bug with dismissAllModalPresenters that caused  a leak in RCTRootView in case the root was replaced while a modal was presented.
Commit 1e48603 already fixed the same issue somehow but it didn't make sense, the actual problem was not waiting for the modal dismiss to occur.

support RN31:
	- a timing issue with RN now requires us to wait until the bridge finishes loading before we can create the RCTRootViews
	- also added the missing import for objc runtime.

related to issue #85 and PR #86
